energycomments: Adjustment = Energy Efficiency Rider.  Fixed Monthly Charge = Basic Facilities Charge + Fixed Monthly Leaf 50C Charge.
name: Residential Time-of-Use RT
description:
Available on a voluntary basis to individually-metered residential customers in residences, condominiums, mobile homes, or apartments which provide independent and permanent facilities for living, sleeping, eating, cooking, and sanitation.
Summer Months are June through September.
Peak hours during summer months are 1 P.M. - 7 P.M. M-F. All other hours, Saturdays, Sundays, and Holidays are considered Off-Peak
Winter Months are October through May.
Peak hours during winter months are 7 A.M. - 12 Noon. M-F. All other hours, Saturdays, Sundays, and Holidays are considered Off-Peak.
